 case of both Georgia and the Basque Country, there is little evidence suggesting the existence of strong, politically organized nationalist opposition to globalization. Globalization and Nationalism discusses why, on a broader scale, different forms of nationalism develop differing attitudes towards globalization and engage in different relationships.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aNationalismzGeorgia (Republic). 0aNationalismzSpainxPaís Vasco. 0aPaís Vasco (Spain)xHistoryxAutonomy and independence movements. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Ideologies / Nationalism & Patriotism.2bisacsh  a21st century, Basque Country, Georgia, Globalization, History, Late 20th century, Nationalism, Political studies, Spain.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCentral European University Press eBook-Package 2013-1998z978311078055040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789633860069423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789633860069/original  a978-3-11-078055-0  Central European University Press eBook-Package 2013-1998c1998d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles